# Forge environment variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:  cp .env.example .env
#
# HOW MODES WORK
# - Set BOTH variables below  -> Forge runs in LIVE mode (Supabase backend).
# - Leave BOTH blank          -> Forge runs in DEMO mode (data stored on-device).
# - Setting only one is a mistake and triggers a startup warning.
#
# The EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix is required so Expo inlines these into the client
# bundle. The Supabase anon key is safe to ship publicly because Row Level
# Security protects all data. NEVER put the service_role key or OPENAI_API_KEY
# in this file — those are server-side secrets.
#
# Where to find these: Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> API
#   Project URL  -> EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
#   anon public  -> EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server-side only — DO NOT set these here. Configure them as Supabase Edge
# Function secrets instead:
#   supabase secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...   OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Smoke test only (scripts/smoke-test.mjs). Used to create + sign in two test
# users against a live project. The service_role key is highly privileged —
# keep it out of the client and out of source control.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
